      • allTerms

        public TermFacetExpression<T> allTerms()

        Specified by:

      • allRanges

        public RangeFacetExpression<T> allRanges()
        Generates an expression to obtain the facet of the attribute for any range. For example: a possible faceted classification could be ["-40": 4, "105": 2, "4": 1]. Notice that this method generates a facet expression with two ranges: (-∞, 0] and [0, +∞), therefore two results should be expected.
        Returns:
        a facet expression for all values
